COBOL VALIDATION PROJECT05
IF ANY FIELD HAS AN ERROR DUMP THE RECORD

CTR	PIC 99.		(ONLY VALUES 1-3)
	88 VAL-CTR			VALUE 1 THRU 3 26 52 95.  	(88 NO PIC BUT NEEDS A VALUE ONLY EQUAL ON NOT EQUAL NOT > OR <)
	88 CTR-INSURANCE	VALUE 1 THRU 3.				(88 ACTS LIKE A BOOLEAN)
	88 VTR-DENTAL		VALUE 26 52 95.
GRADES			PIC X.
		88 VAL-GRADES	VALUE 'A', THRU 'D' 'F'.
		88 PASS GRADES	VALUE 'A' THRU 'D'.
	
	
	IF CTR NOT NUMERIC
		MOVE "MUST BE NUMERIC WITH VALUE OF 1-3" TO O-ERROR
		GO TO EXIT.
	IF NOT VAL-CTR
		MOVE "INVALID VALUE MUST BE 1 TO 3" TO O-ERROR.  (THIS WOULD CRASH IF SPECIAL CHAR OR LETTER).
		
		GO TO EXIT.
	IF CTR-INSURANCE
		PERFORM WHATEVER.
	IF FIRST-NAME EQUAL SPACES
		MOVE ' FIRST NAME IS REQUIRED' TO ERROR
		GO TO EXIT.